handist.collections

Class Bag<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • handist.collections.Bag<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the object handled
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.esotericsoftware.kryo.KryoSerializable, ParallelReceiver<T>, Serializable, Iterable<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DistBag

    public class Bag<T>
extends Object
implements ParallelReceiver<T>, Serializable, com.esotericsoftware.kryo.KryoSerializable
    Container for user-defined types.

    This class implements the ParallelReceiver interface and as such, is capable of concurrently receiving instances of type T from multiple threads. Its use is therefore recommended in parallel implementations of forEach methods.

    See Also:
    Serialized Form

        public void forEach(ExecutorService pool,
                    Consumer<? super T> action)
        Launches a parallel forEach on the elements of this collection. The elements contained in the individual lists (created either through addBag(List) or getReceiver()) are submitted to the provided ExecutorService. This method than waits for the completion of the tasks to return.
        Parameters:
        pool - the executor service in charge of processing this instance
        action - the action to perform on individual elements
